I have reconfigured both `default.conf` and `site.conf` to function as reverse proxies. 

The new configuration intercepts incoming requests on port 80 and forwards them to a designated backend node, while preserving critical client telemetry (Host, Real-IP, and Forwarded-For headers). I have also integrated WebSocket upgrade headers to ensure persistent, bidirectional communication streams remain stable.

The applied configuration is as follows:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name localhost;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080; # Target backend node
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;

        # WebSocket support
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
    }
}
```

